  {
    "id": "b1-separable-verbs",
    "title": "separable verbs",
    "level": "B1",
    "explanation": "Some Dutch verbs split in simple sentences: opbellen becomes ik bel je op. In other forms, the parts can come back together.",
    "examples": [
      {
        "dutch": "Ik bel je later op.",
        "english": "I will call you later."
      },
      {
        "dutch": "Wij komen morgen terug.",
        "english": "We are coming back tomorrow."
      }
    ],
